# Basic Operations in Power BI Query Editor

In this lab, you will practice working with text data and performing basic transformations in Power BI Query Editor, 
such as creating new columns and renaming columns. The main tasks include:
1. Establish a data connection to the AdventureWorks_Products.csv file and create a query named “AW_Product_Lookup” for this dataset.
2. Add a new column named SKUType that extracts all characters between the first “-” and the second “-” in the ProductSKU column.
3. Replace all values of 0 in the ProductStyle column with “NA”.
4. Create a new column named DiscountPrice by multiplying the ProductPrice column by 0.85, representing a 15% discount on the original product price.
